### User API — manual probes (IntelliJ / VS Code REST Client)
#
# Base URL comes from the `baseUri` env var defined in `http-client.env.json`
# (placeholder) or, with the real SUT address, in `http-client.private.env.json`
# (git-ignored). In IntelliJ pick the env in the run gutter; the real URL is never committed.
#
# `{{$timestamp}}` makes username/email unique per send so repeats stay independent.
# Cases marked (BUG-xx) are expected to expose a defect — see docs/defects.md.

### Health check  ->  {"greeting":"..."}
GET {{baseUri}}/

### TC-01  Create user — valid (multipart FormData)  ->  201, user without password
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

user_{{$timestamp}}
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

user_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Secret123
--Boundary--

### TC-04  Create — username missing  ->  400
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

nouser_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Secret123
--Boundary--

### TC-05  Create — username empty ("")  ->  400
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

empty_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Secret123
--Boundary--

### TC-13  Create — all required fields missing  ->  400 (ideally list of all errors; BUG-06 = first only)
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="_"

--Boundary--

### TC-09  Create — malformed email  ->  400 (BUG-02: accepted with 200)
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

bademail_{{$timestamp}}
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

not-an-email
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Secret123
--Boundary--

### TC-12  Create — password too short  ->  400 (BUG-03: accepted with 200)
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

shortpw_{{$timestamp}}
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

shortpw_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

x
--Boundary--

### TC-07/TC-10  Create — duplicate seed (send TWICE: 1st created, 2nd must be rejected 400)
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

dup_user_fixed
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

dup_fixed@example.com
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Secret123
--Boundary--

### TC-14  Create — unknown field role=admin  ->  no 500, no DB internals (BUG-04: 500 leaking SQL/schema)
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

extra_{{$timestamp}}
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

extra_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Secret123
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="role"

admin
--Boundary--

### TC-16  Create — injection strings as data  ->  stored as data, no 500/execution
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=Boundary

--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="username"

' OR 1=1;--<script>alert(1)</script>
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="email"

inject_{{$timestamp}}@example.com
--Boundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="password"

Secret123
--Boundary--

### TC-15  Create — JSON body instead of multipart  ->  400/415 by contract (BUG-10: accepted)
POST {{baseUri}}/user/create
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "json_{{$timestamp}}",
  "email": "json_{{$timestamp}}@example.com",
  "password": "Secret123"
}

### TC-18  Wrong HTTP method on /user/create (GET)  ->  404/405
GET {{baseUri}}/user/create

### TC-20  List users  ->  200, application/json, JSON array (TC-21: items must NOT contain password — BUG-01)
GET {{baseUri}}/user/get

### TC-23  POST on /user/get (GET-only route)  ->  404/405 (BUG-05: 200, returns the list)
POST {{baseUri}}/user/get
